Program: Outlook
Title: Chinese Cultural Revolution 40 Years on
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03kbrzz
Last Broadcast Date: Not available
The legacy and testimony from survivors of China's Cultural Revolution. Also, Interviews with members of Team Shosholoza, the South African sailing team hoping to compete in the Americas Cup yacht race. Uzbeck refugees facing life in exile after the Andijan massacre. The problem of aflatoxin poisoning in Eastern Kenya. Finally, David Lucas the English farmer who builds and exports gallows. Show less